ooks.google.fr/books?id=dHoyBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA33&lpg=PA33|ref=harv}}\n* Kawanami, C. C. (2016). Buddhism . In C. P. Linda Woodhead, ''Religions in the Modern World'' (p.&nbsp;94). New York: Routledge.\n{{refend}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [https://www.shambhala.com/his-holiness-the-fourteenth-dalai-lama A Reader's Guide to the Works of the Dalai Lama (Shambhala Publications)]\n* Dalai Lama. (1991) ''Freedom in Exile: The Autobiography of the Dalai Lama.'' San Francisco, CA.\n* Goodman, Michael H. (1986). ''The Last Dalai Lama''. Shambhala Publications. Boston, MA.\n* [[Heinrich Harrer|Harrer, Heinrich]] (1951) ''[[Seven Years in Tibet]]: My Life Before, During and After''\n* [[Samten Karmay|Karmay, Samten G.]] (Translator) (1988). ''Secret visions of the Fifth Dalai Lama.'' Serindia Publications, London. {{ISBN|0 906026 20 2}}.\n* {{cite book |last1 = Silver |first1 = Murray |title = When Elvis Meets the Dalai Lama |date = 2005 |publisher = Bonaventture |location = Savannah, GA |isbn = 978-0-9724224-4-4 |edition = 1st |ref = harv}}\n* [https://www.quotespedia.org/quotes/authors/d/dalai-lama/ Dalai Lama Quotes]\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Dalai Lamas}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.dalailama.com/}}\n* {{curlie|Society/Religion_and_Spirituality/Buddhism/Lineages/Tibetan/Dalai_Lama/}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{Dalai Lamas}}\n{{TibetanBuddhism}}\n{{Buddhism topics}}\n{{Tibet topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lama, Dalai}}\n[[Category:Dalai Lamas| ]]\n[[Category:Gelug Tulkus]]\n[[Category:Lamas]]\n[[Category:People from Lhasa]]\n[[Category:Politics of Tibet]]\n[[Category:Tibetan Buddhist titles]]\n[[Category:Buddhist religious leaders]]\n[[Category:Deified people]]\n[[Category:Bodhisattvas]]\n[[Category:Avalokite\u015bvara]]\n[[Category:Buddhists]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1700:f29:4090:1dec:7d2d:848b:a85d", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dalai_Lama"}
{"title_page": "List of accolades received by Joker (2019 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of accolades received by ''Joker'' (2019 film)}}\n{{Use American English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use list-defined references|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox awards list\n| title        = List of accolades received by ''Joker''\n| film         = y\n| total_width  = 190\n| image1       = Joaquin Phoenix in 2018.jpg\n| alt1         = \n| caption      = [[Joaquin Phoenix]] won an [[Academy Award]] for his performance as the Joker\n| wins         = 89\n| nominations  = 217\n| awards       = \n{{Custom award|[[Academy Awards]]|2|11}}\n{{Custom award|[[American Society of Cinematographers]]|0|1}}\n{{Custom award|[[Art Directors Guild Awards]]|0|1}}\n{{Custom award|[[British Academy Film Awards]]|3|11}}\n{{Custom award|[[Critics Choice Movie Awards]]|2|7}}\n{{Custom award|Gold Derby Awards|2|7}}\n{{Custom award|[[Golden Globe Awards]]|2|4}}\n{{Custom award|[[Guild of Music Supervisors Awards]]|1|1}}\n{{Custom award|[[Guinness World Records]]|2|2}}\n{{Custom award|[[Palm Springs International Film Festival]]|2|2}}\n{{Custom award|[[Producers Guild of America Award]]|0|1}}\n{{Custom award|[[Satellite Awards]]|2|10}}\n{{Custom award|[[Screen Actors Guild Awards]]|1|2}}\n{{Custom award|[[Writers Guild of America Awards]]|0|1}}\n}}\n''[[Joker (2019 film)|Joker]]'' is a 2019 American [[psychological thriller]] film<!--Do not add more genres per [[WP:FILMLEAD]]--> directed and produced by [[Todd Phillips]], who co-wrote the screenplay with [[Scott Silver]]. The film was produced by [[Warner Bros. Pictures]], [[DC Films]], and Joint Effort, in association with [[Bron Studios|Bron Creative]] and [[Village Roadshow Pictures]], and distributed by Warner Bros. Based on [[DC Comics]] characters, the film stars [[Joaquin Phoenix]] as the [[Joker (character)|Joker]]. Set in 1981, it follows Arthur Fleck, a failed stand-up comedian whose descent into insanity and nihilism inspires a violent countercultural revolution against the wealthy in a decaying [[Gotham City]]. [[Robert De Niro]], [[Zazie Beetz]], [[Frances Conroy]], [[Brett Cullen]], [[Glenn Fleshler]], [[Bill Camp]], [[Shea Whigham]], and [[Marc Maron]] appear in supporting roles.\n\n''Joker'' premiered at the [[76th Venice International Film Festival]] on August 31, 2019, where it won the [[Golden Lion]], and was released in the United States on October 4, 2019. The film polarized critics; while Phoenix's performance, musical score, cinematography and production values were praised, the dark tone, portrayal of mental illness, and handling of violence divided responses.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2019/10/03/why-joker-became-one-most-divisive-movies-year/|title=Why 'Joker' became one of the most divisive movies of the year|last=Cavna|first=Michael|date=October 3, 2019|website=[[The Washington Post]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=October 3, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191003213559/https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2019/10/03/why-joker-became-one-most-divisive-movies-year/|archive-date=October 3, 2019}}</ref> The film became a major box office success, setting records for an October release and grossing over $1 billion, making it the first [[List of highest-grossing R-rated films|R-rated film]] to pass the billion-dollar mark at the worldwide box office, the [[2019 in film#Highest-grossing films|sixth-highest-grossing film of 2019]], and the [[List of highest-grossing films|31st-highest-grossing film]] of all time. At the [[92nd Academy Awards]], the film earned a leading 11 nominations (including [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]), winning [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] for Phoenix and [[Academy Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]] for [[Hildur Gu\u00f0nad\u00f3ttir]]. Phoenix and Gu\u00f0nad\u00f3ttir also won at the [[Golden Globe]] and [[BAFTA Award]] ceremonies. The [[American Film Institute]] selected ''Joker'' as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2019#Top 10 Films|top 10 films of 2019]].\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-<!--AWARDS CEREMONIES ARE IN ALPHABETICAL ORDER-->\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" scope=\"row\"| [[AACTA Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[9th AACTA International Awards|January 3, 2020]]\n| [[AACTA International Award for Best Film|Best International Film]]\n|''Joker''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/aacta-international-awards-2019-nominations-full-list-1202805679/|title=AACTA International Awards Nominations Led By 'The Irishman', 'Hollywood', 'Joker' & 'Parasite'|last=Tartaglione|first=Nancy|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=December 10, 2019|accessdate=December 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191210222327/https://deadline.com/2019/12/aacta-international-awards-2019-nominations-full-list-1202805679/|archive-date=December 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/parasite-named-best-picture-by-australias-aacta-awards-1266148|title='Parasite' Named Best Picture by Australia's AACTA Awards|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Etan|last=Vlessing|date=January 3, 2020|accessdate=January 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200104035938/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/parasite-named-best-picture-by-australias-aacta-awards-1266148|archive-date=January 4, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[AACTA International Award for Best Direction|Best International Direction]]\n| [[Todd Phillips]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[AACTA International Award for Best Screenplay|Best International Screenplay]]\n| Todd Phillips, [[Scott Silver]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[AACTA International Award for Best Actor|Best International Actor]]\n| [[Joaquin Phoenix]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[AARP#AARP Awards|AARP's Movies for Grownups Awards]]\n| January 11, 2020\n| Readers\u2019 Choice\n|''Joker''\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aarp.org/entertainment/movies-for-grownups/info-2020/annual-film-awards-nominations.html?intcmp=AE-ENT-M4G-BB|title=2019 Movies for Grownups Awards Nominees|last=Appelo|first=Tim|website=[[AARP]]|date=November 26, 2019|accessdate=November 27, 2019}}</ref><br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aarp.org/entertainment/movies-for-grownups/info-2020/annual-film-awards-winners.html|title=2019 Movies for Grownups Award Winners|last=Appelo|first=Tim|website=[[AARP]]|date=January 12, 2020|accessdate=January 12, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112071150/https://www.aarp.org/entertainment/movies-for-grownups/info-2020/annual-film-awards-winners.html|archive-date=January 12, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"11\" scope=\"row\" |[[Academy Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"11\" | [[92nd Academy Awards|February 9, 2020]]\n| [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\n| [[Bradley Cooper]], Todd Phillips, [[Emma Tillinger Koskoff]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"11\" style=\"text-align: center\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/13/movies/oscar-nominations-academy-awards.html|title=Oscar Nominations 2020: \u2018Joker\u2019 and \u2018Irishman\u2019 Lead the Nominees|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=January 13, 2020|accessdate=January 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114120904/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/13/movies/oscar-nominations-academy-awards.html|archive-date=January 14, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><br/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/2020-oscars-winners-list-92-academy-awards-1202855067/|title=Oscars: \u2018Parasite\u2019 Wins Best Picture \u2013 The Complete Winners List|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=February 9, 2020|accessdate=February 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| Todd Phillips\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]\n| Todd Phillips, Scott Silver\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| Joaquin Phoenix\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n| [[Lawrence Sher]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Makeup and Hairstyling|Best Makeup and Hairstyling]]\n| Nicki Ledermann, Kay Georgiou\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Costume Design|Best Costume Design]]\n| [[Mark Bridges (costume designer)|Mark Bridges]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Film Editing|Best Film Editing]]\n| [[Jeff Groth (film editor)|Jeff Groth]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Original Score|Best Original Score]]\n| [[Hildur Gu\u00f0nad\u00f3ttir]]\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Sound Editing|Best Sound Editing]]\n| [[Alan Robert Murray]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Award for Best Sound Mixing|Best Sound Mixing]]\n| Tom Ozanich, [[Dean A. Zupancic|Dean Zupancic]], [[Tod A. Maitland|Tod Maitland]]\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]]\n| January 10, 2020\n| [[Alliance of Women Film Journalists Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| Joaquin Phoenix\n| {{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nextbestpicture.com/latest/the-2019-alliance-of-women-film-journalists-awfj-eda-awards-nominations|title=The 2019 Alliance Of Women Film Journalists (AWFJ) EDA Awards Nominations|last=Neglia|first=Matt|website=Next Best Picture|date=December 20, 2019|accessdate=December 20, 2019|archive-